<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-16T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-16T03:00:00-05:00" n="853" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d853">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Strong, Robert C.: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Strong</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of state</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-16T16:00:00+08:00">December 16,
                                1949—4 p. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received December 16—9:39 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Cantel 1337. Reference Cantel 1336, December 15, repeated Taipei 247. Am
                        proceeding Taipei with O’Grady on SS <hi rend="italic">Shenking</hi>,
                        departing Hong Kong December 20, arriving Keelung December 22.</p>
                    <p>Request Department circularize interested posts to direct telegraphic
                        communications for Embassy to Taipei from December 19. Sent Department
                        Cantel 1337, repeated Taipei 248.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Strong</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>